儘管2016年的階段看起來是安全的，但在2016年1月宣布，當前的財務狀況可能會使2018年的任務要延遲2年<ref name="Delaying 20182">{{cite news|url=http://www.industryweek.com/emerging-technologies/money-troubles-may-delay-europe-russia-mars-mission|title=Money Troubles May Delay Europe-Russia Mars Mission|work=Agence France-Presse|publisher=Industry Week|date=2016-01-15|accessdate=2016-01-16|archive-date=2020-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201184900/http://www.industryweek.com/emerging-technologies/money-troubles-may-delay-europe-russia-mars-mission|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Delaying2018-spnews2">{{cite web|title=Proton launches Euro-Russian ExoMars mission, but program’s second launch remains in limbo|url=http://spacenews.com/proton-launches-euro-russian-exomars-mission-but-programs-second-launch-remains-in-limbo/|accessdate=2016-03-15|website=Spacenews.com}}</ref>。義大利對火星探測計畫的貢獻最大，英國是任務的第二大的金融靠山<ref name="closing $ gap2">{{cite news|first=Stephen|last=Clark|title=Facing funding gap, ExoMars rover is on schedule for now|date=2014-03-03|url=http://www.spaceflightnow.com/news/n1403/03exomars/|work=Spaceflight Now|accessdate=2016-03-19|archive-date=2019-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209232327/https://spaceflightnow.com/news/n1403/03exomars/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。俄羅斯的火星探測計畫融資可以由[[福布斯－土壤|福布斯－土壤]]損失的保險支付部分，大約是12億盧布（4070萬美金）<ref name="Gazeta2" />，和重新分配與調整用於[[Mars-NET|Mars-NET]]和火星探測計畫的資金<ref>{{cite web|title=The Mars-NET project|url=http://www.russianspaceweb.com/marsnet.html|accessdate=2012-04-18|date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508072732/http://russianspaceweb.com/marsnet.html|archive-date=2012-05-08|dead-url=no|quote=Possible coordination between Mars-NET and European ExoMars project.}}</ref><ref name="Mars-Grunt2">{{cite news|first=Ilya|last=Kramnik|title=Russia takes a two-pronged approach to space exploration|date=2012-04-18|url=http://indrus.in/articles/2012/04/18/russia_takes_a_two-pronged_approach_to_space_exploration_15511.html|work=Russia & India Report|accessdate=2016-03-19|archive-date=2012-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422080732/http://indrus.in/articles/2012/04/18/russia_takes_a_two-pronged_approach_to_space_exploration_15511.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

到目前為止，最初歐洲航天局已經挹注火星探測計畫10億歐元（13億美金），但是NASA的撤出和合資企業的重組，隨後可能將添加數億歐元的支出，所以在2012年3月，該機構會員國的行政部門已經指示，看看要如何才可以弭補此一不足<ref>{{cite news|first=Peter B.|last=de Selding|title=ESA Eyeing Hodgepodge of Funding Sources To Save ExoMars Mission|date=2012-05-31|url=http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120531-hodgepodge-funding-save-exomars.html|work=Space News|accessdate=2016-03-19|archive-date=2012-09-10|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120910163843/http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120531-hodgepodge-funding-save-exomars.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。一個可能是歐洲航天局的其他科學活動稍微退讓一下，使火星探測計畫獲得優先<ref>{{cite web|title=ExoMars Wins One-month Reprieve|url=http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120516-exomars-one-month-reprieve.html|date=2012-05-16|work=Space News|access-date=2016-03-19|archive-date=2012-09-13|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120913122819/http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120516-exomars-one-month-reprieve.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。在2012年9月，歐洲航天局宣布它的新成員，波蘭和羅馬尼亞，將貢獻七千万歐元資助火星探測計畫<ref>{{cite news|first=Peter B.|last=de Selding|title=Poland Tripling Space Spending in Bid To Boost Economy|date=2012-09-19|url=http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120919-poland-tripling-space-spending.html|work=Space News}}{{Dead link}}</ref>。儘管是在一個相對次要的角色，歐洲航天局並沒有排除NASA重回2018火星探測計畫的可能性 <ref name="Selding2">{{cite news|first=Peter B.|last=de Selding|title=ESA Ruling Council OKs ExoMars Funding|date=2012-03-15|url=http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120315-esa-council-oks-exomars.html|work=Space News|accessdate=2016-03-18|archive-date=2012-12-06|archive-url=https://archive.today/20121206010858/http://www.spacenews.com/civil/120315-esa-council-oks-exomars.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Morning2">{{cite news|first=Frank|last=Morring, Jr.|title=Appropriators Blocking Mars Mission Move|date=2012-03-08|url=http://www.aviationweek.com/aw/generic/story_channel.jsp?channel=space&id=news/awx/2012/03/08/awx_03_08_2012_p0-434301.xml&headline=Appropriators%20Blocking%20Mars%20Mission%20Move|work=[[Aviation_Week|Aviation Week]]}}</ref>。

截至2014年3月，主導火星探測計畫漫遊車製造的[[空中巴士防務及航太公司|空中巴士防務及航太公司]]英國分公司，已經開始採購關鍵的零件<ref name="closing $ gap2" />。2018漫遊車一億歐元（1.38億美金）的資金仍然短少<ref name="closing $ gap2" />，由[[加拿大太空局|加拿大太空局]]支付的車輪和懸吊系統現在已經開始在加拿大的{{Tsl|en|MDA_(company)|麦克唐纳•迪特维利联合有限公司}}製造<ref name="closing $ gap2" />。

ExoMars-2016发射任务执行前，因2015年[[質子M型運載火箭|質子M型運載火箭]]發射了100架次，有10次失敗的失败率<ref name="Failures2">{{cite news|last=de Selding|first=Peter B.|url=http://spacenews.com/36138profile-alexander-seliverstov-general-director-khrunichev-state-research-and/|title=Alexander Seliverstov, General Director, Khrunichev State Research and Production Space Center|work=Space News|date=2013-07-08|accessdate=2015-05-16|quote=Prior to the July 2 launch failure, the Proton rocket had been rebounding from a series of launch anomalies that already had forced up commercial Proton insurance rates and caused anxiety in a global market that, for now, relies on Proton and Europe's Ariane 5 heavy-lift vehicle for the majority of commercial launch services.}}</ref><ref name="reliability2">{{cite news|last=Amos|first=Jonathan|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32763724|title=Russian rocket carrying satellite burns up over Siberia|work=BBC News|date=2015-05-16|accessdate=2015-05-16|quote=Russia used to be a byword in reliability for space technology, but its reputation has taken a hammering recently. Proton rockets now fail with alarming regularity.|archive-date=2016-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208080722/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32763724|dead-url=no}}</ref>，質子運載火箭發射的[[質子M型運載火箭|可靠性]]遭到质疑<ref name="Unreliable20152">{{cite news|last=Klotz|first=Irene|url=http://sen.com/news/russian-rocket-failure-casts-pall-on-european-mars-missions|title=Russian rocket failure casts pall on European Mars missions|work=Spaceflight Insider|publisher=Space Exploration Network (SEN)|date=2015-05-16|accessdate=2015-05-16|archive-date=2016-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160402200503/http://sen.com/news/russian-rocket-failure-casts-pall-on-european-mars-missions|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="concerns2">{{cite news|last=Sutherland|first=Paul|url=http://sen.com/news/exomars-team-press-on-as-inquest-begins-into-proton-crash|title=ExoMars team press on as inquest begins into Proton crash|work=SEN News|date=2015-05-19|accessdate=2015-05-20|archive-date=2016-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310111117/http://sen.com/news/exomars-team-press-on-as-inquest-begins-into-proton-crash|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== ExoMars-2016发射任务 ===
2016年3月14日，执行ExoMars-2016发射任务的[[質子M型運載火箭|質子M型運載火箭]]成功点火升空（從08:30GMT[[直播|直播]]）<ref name="NYT-20160314">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title=Mars Mission Blasts Off From Kazakhstan |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/15/science/mars-mission-blasts-off-from-kazakhstan.html |date=2016-03-14 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |accessdate=2016-03-14 |archive-date=2016-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318072936/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/15/science/mars-mission-blasts-off-from-kazakhstan.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ESA-2016">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Watch ExoMars Launch (March 14, 2016, 08:30 GMT [03:30 AM EDT] |url=http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/ExoMars/Watch_ExoMars_launch |date=2016-03-10 |work=[[European_Space_Agency|European Space Agency]] |accessdate=2016-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311082709/http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/ExoMars/Watch_ExoMars_launch |archive-date=2016-03-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="LS-20160314">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Live Video - ExoMars Launch (March 14, 2016, 08:30 GMT) |url=http://livestream.com/ESA/exomars |date=2016-03-14 |work=[[Livestream|Livestream]] |accessdate=2016-03-10 |archive-date=2016-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317224142/http://livestream.com/ESA/exomars |dead-url=no }}</ref>，[[火星微量氣體任務衛星|火星微量氣體任務衛星]]运行状态良好<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/ExoMars/ExoMars_on_its_way_to_solve_the_Red_Planet_s_mysteries |title=ExoMars on its way to solve the Red Planet's mysteries |publisher=ESA |date=2016-03-14 |accessdate=2016-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026085720/http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/ExoMars/ExoMars_on_its_way_to_solve_the_Red_Planet_s_mysteries |archive-date=2016-10-26 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。2016年10月19日，火星微量氣體任務衛星抵达[[火星轨道|火星轨道]]，并于10月16日释放了[[斯基亞帕雷利EDM登陸器|斯基亞帕雷利EDM登陸器]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=ExoMars TGO reaches Mars orbit while EDM situation under assessment|url=https://www.esa.int/Science_Exploration/Human_and_Robotic_Exploration/Exploration/ExoMars/ExoMars_TGO_reaches_Mars_orbit_while_EDM_situation_under_assessment|access-date=2022-03-23|date=2016-10-19|publisher=欧洲空间局|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323124522/https://www.esa.int/Science_Exploration/Human_and_Robotic_Exploration/Exploration/ExoMars/ExoMars_TGO_reaches_Mars_orbit_while_EDM_situation_under_assessment|archive-date=2022-03-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此后，该着陆器着陆时與火星发生高速碰撞，造成登陸計劃失敗<ref name=":0" />。2016年10月21日，美國宇航局發布了一張[[火星侦察轨道器|火星偵察軌道衛星]]的圖像，顯示了著陸器墜毀地點<ref name=":5" />。

=== ExoMars-2022发射任务 ===
2018年<ref name=":22">{{Cite web|title=N° 11–2016: Second ExoMars mission moves to next launch opportunity in 2020|url=https://www.esa.int/Newsroom/Press_Releases/Second_ExoMars_mission_moves_to_next_launch_opportunity_in_2020|access-date=2022-03-19|date=2016-05-02|publisher=欧洲空间局|language=en|archive-url=https://archive.today/20220319064613/https://www.esa.int/Newsroom/Press_Releases/Second_ExoMars_mission_moves_to_next_launch_opportunity_in_2020|archive-date=2022-03-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>与2020年<ref name=":32">{{Cite web|title=ExoMars to take off for the Red Planet in 2022|url=https://www.esa.int/Newsroom/Press_Releases/ExoMars_to_take_off_for_the_Red_Planet_in_2022|access-date=2022-03-19|date=2020-03-12|publisher=欧洲空间局|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220319062237/https://www.esa.int/Newsroom/Press_Releases/ExoMars_to_take_off_for_the_Red_Planet_in_2022|archive-date=2022-03-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[欧洲空间局|欧洲空间局]]两次延期了第二次的发射任务，并最后将发射时间定于2022年，任务代号{{Lang|en|ExoMars-2022}}。2022年3月，欧空局宣布受[[2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭|2022年俄羅斯入侵烏克蘭]]影响，欧方暂停与俄方合作、暂停原定于2022年9月的第二次发射任务<ref name=":4" />。

== 任務目標 ==
[[科學|科學的]]目標依優先順序如下<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.esa.int/SPECIALS/ExoMars/SEM0VIAMS7F_0.html |title=Scientific objectives - ExoMars |date=2007-11-01 |publisher=European Space Agency (ESA) |access-date=2010-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019170339/http://www.esa.int/SPECIALS/ExoMars/SEM0VIAMS7F_0.html |archive-date=2012-10-19 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>：
* 尋找在過去或現在的[[火星生命|火星生命]]可能的[[生物標記|生物標記]]。
* 確定火星淺層地表下[[火星水文|火星的水]]和[[地球化學|地球化學]]與深度相關的分布狀態。
* 研究表面環境並研判對未來[[載人火星任務|載人火星任務]]的危害性。
* 探討這顆行星表層和深層的內部，以更好的理解其演化和適居性。
* 逐步實現最終將火星樣本取回的任務。

發展的技術目標是：
* 增加登陸火星的[[有效酬載_(航空和太空)|酬載]]。
* 在火星上利用[[太陽能|太陽電力]]。
* 利用鑽孔機能夠收集地下深度達到{{convert|2|m|ft}}的樣品。這個深度的岩石不會受到紫外線、氧化與高能離子分解<ref name="September 2009 status">{{Cite book|last=J.L.Vago|contribution=Mars Panel Meeting|title=Planetary Science Decadal Survey|publisher=[[ESA|ESA]]|place=Arizona State University, Tempe (USA)|date=2009-09-10|contribution-url=http://www.marspages.eu/media/archive4/exomars/statusbericht/StatusberichtSep2009.pdf|accessdate=2009-11-24|archive-date=2015-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150930130748/https://www.marspages.eu/media/archive4/exomars/statusbericht/StatusberichtSep2009.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。
* 開發有地表勘探能力的漫遊車。

